blurhash
------------------------------------------
Simple encoder and decoder for blurhashes

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.6-1
  libblurhash-devel-0.2.0-1bl1
  libblurhash0.2-0.2.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.9.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.40-1
  cygport-0.36.1-1
  doctest-2.4.8-1bl1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  meson-0.63.3-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://nheko.im/nheko-reborn/blurhash

Canonical download:
  https://nheko.im/nheko-reborn/blurhash/-/archive/v0.2.0/blurhash-v0.2.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack blurhash-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./blurhash-0.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/blurhash-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/blurhash-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libblurhash0.2-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libblurhash-devel-0.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(blurhash)
  /usr/bin/blurhash.exe
  /usr/bin/blurhash2bmp.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/blurhash.README
  /usr/share/doc/blurhash/CHANGELOG.md
  /usr/share/doc/blurhash/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/blurhash/README.md

(libblurhash0.2)
  /usr/bin/cygblurhash-0.2.dll

(libblurhash-devel)
  /usr/include/blurhash.hpp
  /usr/lib/libblurhash.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/blurhash.pc

------------------

